The bandits are reported to have also invaded the staff quarters and abducted an elderly woman. The school is located in the home state of President Muhammadu Buhari. Bandits have attacked a boarding secondary school in Kandara, Katsina, the home state of President Muhammadu Buhari, abducting 54 male students. 
The bandits were reported to have invaded Government Science Secondary School, at 10pm on Friday, December 11, 2020, the day President Buhari arrived in his home for a week-long rest.



